  "texts": [
    "For ⊑-forth, since F is a possibility frame, we have that for all X ∈ P, F satisfies the L 1 (I, P) sentence ∀x∀y((y ⊑ x ∧ Ẋ(x)) → Ẋ(y)), so its L 1 (I, P)elementary extension F s does as well.",
    "Now if y ⊑ ′ x, so y ⊑ s x, then since F s satisfies the given sentence, it follows by the definition of g that g(y) ⊇ g(x), so g(y)⊑ (F b) f g(x).The proof of R-forth is analogous, using for every X ∈ P the sentence ∀x∀y((x Ṙi y ∧ (■ i X)(x)) → Ẋ(y)), where (■ i X) is the predicate symbol corresponding to ■ i X in P, and then the definition of R(F b) f i.",
    "For ⊑-back, suppose that F ⊑ (F b) f g(x), so F is a filter in F b such that F ⊇ g(x).",
    "Expand the language L 1 (Φ, P) with a new constant symbol ẋ.",
    "Let Σ = { Ẋ(y) | X ∈ F } ∪ {y ⊑ ẋ}."
